instruction: I like to host guests at my home from time to time, and I am gathering  recipes of different dishes and drinks to keep things interesting. I am interested in trying some Danish dishes. Can you give me a recipe for Flæskesteg?
output_1:
Ingredients:
-4 pounds pork shoulder roast
-3 tablespoons salt
-3 tablespoons freshly ground pepper
-3 tablespoons caraway seeds
-Optional: 8 slices of bacon

Instructions:
1. Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).
2. Place pork shoulder roast in a roasting pan.
3. Rub salt, pepper, and caraway seeds all over the pork roast.
4. If desired, lay bacon slices over the top of the roast.
5. Roast in preheated oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until an instant-read thermometer inserted into the center of the roast reads 145 degrees F (63 degrees C).
6. Allow roast to rest for 10 minutes before slicing and serving. Enjoy!
output_2:
Flæskesteg (Roast Pork with Crackling) is a traditional Danish Christmas dish made with roasted pork belly seasoned with salt, pepper, allspice and cloves. The cracklings are crispy and delicious when served alongside the tender meat. It can be served as part of a larger feast or enjoyed on its own as a hearty main course. Here's how to make it:
Ingredients:
- 2 kg/4 lb pork belly
- Salt
- Peppercorns
- Allspice berries
- Clove sticks
Instructions:
1. Preheat oven to 200°C/395°F.
2. Rub the pork belly liberally with salt and pepper. Place the allspice berries and clove sticks into small openings along the length of the pork belly.
3. Place the pork onto a rack over a baking sheet lined with foil. Insert two more pieces of foil underneath the rack so that any juices will not leak out while cooking.
4. Roast in preheated oven until the internal temperature reaches 75–80°C/165–170°F, about 2 hours.
5. Remove from oven and let cool slightly before slicing thinly against the grain. Serve warm with your favorite side dishes. Enjoy!

instruction: Please tell me about the romantic relationship between Julius Caesar and Cleopatra.
output_1: Julius Caesar and Cleopatra had a passionate and complex romantic relationship. The two first became acquainted when Julius Caesar visited Egypt in 48 BC when Cleopatra was only 18. It is said that Cleopatra was so captivating that Julius instantly fell in love with her. After their first meeting, Caesar and Cleopatra became inseparable. They shared a deep bond, with Caesar taking Cleopatra as his mistress and visiting her often. Caesar even went so far as to have a palace built for Cleopatra, the Caesarion, in Alexandria. The two had a son together, Caesarion, in 47 BC, and Caesar celebrated this with a triumphal procession in Rome. Their relationship continued until Caesar's assassination in 44 BC, when Cleopatra was forced to flee Egypt.
output_2: Julius Caesar and Cleopatra had a passionate, but ultimately doomed, love affair which began in 59 BCE when Julius was serving as governor of Roman-controlled Egypt. The two were immediately drawn to each other; Julius described her as “the most beautiful woman he ever saw.” They quickly became lovers despite their cultural differences – Julius being a Roman and Cleopatra an Egyptian – and their age difference (Cleopatra was only 18 at the time). Their relationship lasted for several years until Julius’s death in 44 BCE. After his assassination, she mourned him deeply and even attempted suicide by poisoning herself with an asp. She eventually gave up on life and allowed herself to be defeated by Octavian, who then took control of Egypt. Despite this tragic ending, it is said that they shared a deep bond of love and respect throughout their short-lived relationship.

instruction: Hi, I'm in the mood for a Bloody Mary. Can you give me a recipe for making one?
output_1:
Ingredients:
- 4 ounces tomato juice
- 1 ounce vodka
- 2 dashes Worcestershire sauce
- 2 dashes hot sauce
- 1/4 teaspoon horseradish
- 1/4 teaspoon celery salt
- 1/4 teaspoon ground black pepper
- 1/2 lemon, juiced
- Garnish of celery stalk and lemon wedge

Instructions:
1. Fill a highball glass with ice.
2. Pour in the tomato juice, vodka, Worcestershire sauce, hot sauce, horseradish, celery salt, and pepper.
3. Stir to combine.
4. Squeeze in the lemon juice.
5. Garnish with a celery stalk and a lemon wedge.
6. Enjoy your Bloody Mary!
output_2:
Ingredients: 2 oz vodka, 1/4 cup tomato juice, 3 dashes Worcestershire sauce, 1 teaspoon celery salt, 1 lime wedge, black pepper to taste, hot sauce of your choice (optional)
Instructions:
Fill a shaker with ice cubes. Pour the vodka and tomato juice into the shaker. Shake vigorously until combined. Strain the mixture into a chilled glass over more ice. Add the Worcestershire sauce, celery salt, lime wedge, and black pepper to taste. Garnish with a lemon or orange slice and a sprinkle of hot sauce if desired. Enjoy!

instruction: what are some good ways to spread ashes?
output_1:
1. Bury the ashes in a cemetery or memorial park.
2. Scatter the ashes in a meaningful location, such as a favorite spot of the deceased or a place they loved to visit.
3. Place the ashes in a biodegradable urn and float them on a body of water.
4. Place the ashes in an urn and bury them at sea.
5. Place the ashes in an artificial reef and drop them into the ocean.
6. Create a memorial diamond or glass sculpture with the ashes.
7. Place the ashes in a special keepsake such as a locket or pendant.
8. Create a living memorial by planting a tree with the ashes.
9. Place the ashes in fireworks and scatter them into the sky.
10. Create a memorial piece of artwork with the ashes.
output_2:
1. Into the sea - scattering cremated remains into the ocean can be a meaningful way of saying farewell and letting go, with the waves taking your loved one's ashes out to sea. 
2. On land – you could choose to bury or inter scattered ashes on private property such as in a garden, at a special place or memorial site, or even in a favorite spot. You may also want to consider creating a permanent memorial for your loved ones by having their ashes placed in a columbarium niche or other type of urn vault. 
3. High up – if you’d like to honor your loved one’s memory while experiencing beautiful views, sky diving might be just what you need! Many companies offer skydiving packages where participants can take along small amounts of ash from their departed family members which they then release during freefall. 
4. Up high – hot air ballooning offers another unique option for those who would like to pay tribute to lost loved ones. Balloon rides typically last around an hour and allow passengers to ascend hundreds of feet above ground level before releasing the ashes near the landing area. 
5. Out of this world – space burial allows families to send cremation ashes into orbit aboard a dedicated rocket. The launches usually occur over the Pacific Ocean and provide a truly memorable experience for friends and family.

instruction: I like to host guests at my home from time to time, and I am gathering  recipes of different dishes and drinks to keep things interesting. I am interested in trying some Ukrainian dishes. Can you give me a recipe for Okroshka?
output_1:
Okroshka Recipe:
Ingredients:
-2 eggs
-1 medium cucumber, diced
-1/2 medium onion, diced
-1/2 cup diced cooked potatoes
-1/2 cup diced cooked carrots
-1/2 cup diced cooked beets
-1/2 cup diced cooked ham
-1/2 cup diced cooked sausage
-1/4 cup diced dill pickle
-1/2 cup kefir or sour cream
-2 tablespoons prepared mustard
-Salt and pepper to taste

Instructions:
1. Boil the eggs until hard-boiled and let cool. Peel and chop into cubes.
2. Mix together the cucumber, onion, potatoes, carrots, beets, ham, sausage, and pickle in a large bowl.
3. In a separate bowl, whisk together the kefir or sour cream, mustard, salt, and pepper.
4. Pour the kefir mixture slowly over the vegetables and mix until everything is evenly coated.
5. Gently fold in the chopped eggs.
6. Serve cold. Enjoy!
output_2:
Okroshka (Ukrainian cold soup)
Ingredients:
-2 cups shredded cabbage
-1/4 cup grated carrot
-3 tablespoons olive oil
-Salt & pepper to taste
-1/2 teaspoon sugar
-1/2 cup sour cream
Instructions:
1. In a large bowl combine all ingredients except sour cream. Stir until everything is evenly mixed together.
2. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight or up to one day before serving.
3. When ready to serve, add sour cream and stir gently. Taste and adjust seasonings if necessary. Serve chilled.

instruction: I like to host guests at my home from time to time, and I am gathering  recipes of different dishes and drinks to keep things interesting. I am interested in trying some Danish dishes. Can you give me a recipe for Koldskål?
output_1:
Ingredients:
- 4 cups of cold buttermilk 
- 2 tablespoons of sugar 
- 1 teaspoon of ground cinnamon 
- 2 tablespoons of chopped almonds 
- 2 tablespoons of raisins 
- 3 tablespoons of diced apple 

Instructions:
1. In a large bowl, mix together the buttermilk and sugar until blended.
2. Add the ground cinnamon, almonds, raisins, and diced apple. Stir until all ingredients are combined.
3. Chill the mixture for at least 1 hour before serving.
4. Serve the Koldskål in individual glasses or bowls. Enjoy!
output_2: Koldskål (literally "cold soup") is a traditional Danish cold vegetable soup made with potatoes, carrots, onions, celery, green peas, and cream. It can be served as a main course or as part of a larger dinner party menu. The ingredients are boiled until tender then blended together with the cream. This mixture is chilled before serving. To make it more flavorful, add herbs such as thyme, rosemary, parsley, oregano, or tarragon. You may also want to season it with salt and pepper. Serve this delicious soup with crusty bread or crackers. Enjoy!

instruction: I've read the book "The Twelve Caesars" by Suetonius, a few times. I'm curious about the context, of when he wrote.
output_1: Suetonius wrote The Twelve Caesars during the early 2nd century AD. It is a biographical work that details the lives and reigns of the first twelve Roman emperors, from Julius Caesar to Domitian. The work was initially published in 121 AD, though it was probably written between 110 and 130 AD.
output_2: Suetonius was born around 69 CE in the Roman province of Africa and died sometime after 122 CE. He served as a court official under Emperor Hadrian (reigned 117-38 CE) before retiring to write his famous work The Lives of the Caesars or De Vita Caesarum ("Lives of the Twelve Caesars"). This work covers the lives of Julius Caesar, Augustus, Tiberius, Caligula, Claudius, Nero, Galba, Otho, Vitellius, Vespasian, Titus, Domitian, and finally himself. It provides valuable insight into the reigns of these emperors and their impact on Rome during this period. His other works include a biography of Trajan and a collection of historical anecdotes entitled Parallela Historia. Little else is known about him beyond what can be gleaned from his writings.

instruction: Please tell me the history of Walt Disney.
output_1:
Walt Disney began his career in animation in the early 1920s. He and his brother, Roy, created the Disney Brothers' Studio in 1923, which later became The Walt Disney Company. His first major success was the creation of the character Mickey Mouse in 1928. Throughout the 1930s, Disney produced a number of successful animated films, including Snow White and the Seven Dwarfs, Pinocchio, Dumbo, and Fantasia. 

In the 1940s, Disney began to focus more on live-action films, producing a number of classic films such as Treasure Island and The Three Caballeros. He also created the Disneyland theme park in 1955. In the 1960s, Disney produced a number of live-action films, including The Parent Trap and Mary Poppins. He also began to create the first Disney animated films in color, including The Jungle Book and The Aristocats. 

The 1970s saw the release of a number of Disney classics, including Robin Hood, The Rescuers, and The Fox and the Hound. In the 1980s, Disney released a number of successful animated films, including The Little Mermaid, Beauty and the Beast, and The Lion King. The 1990s were a time of expansion for the company, with the opening of Disney World in Florida and the purchase of a number of major media companies, including ABC and ESPN. 

In the 2000s, Disney continued to produce animated films, such as Lilo & Stitch and Finding Nemo, as well as the first Pirates of the Caribbean movie. The company also expanded its presence in Asia, opening several theme parks in China and Japan. In the 2010s, Disney released a number of successful films, including Frozen, Zootopia, and Moana. The company also acquired a number of major media companies, such as Marvel, Lucasfilm, and 21st Century Fox.
output_2: Walter Elias "Walt" Disney (December 5, 1901 – December 15, 1966) was an American entrepreneur and animator who founded The Walt Disney Company in 1923. He was one of the most influential figures in animation and entertainment, helping to create some of the world's best-known characters including Mickey Mouse, Donald Duck, Goofy, Pluto, Snow White, Cinderella, Sleeping Beauty, and Peter Pan. His films have won numerous awards and accolades, and he has received four honorary Academy Awards for his contributions to cinema. In addition to being a successful businessman, Disney was also a visionary when it came to technology; he pioneered techniques such as multiplane camera work and synthetic sound. After his death in 1966, Disney's legacy continued through his company which now includes theme parks, television networks, and other media properties around the globe.

instruction: Can you help me figure out how to sew a button on a shirt?
output_1:
1. Gather your supplies: a needle, thread, and a button.
2. Thread your needle, and tie a knot at the end of the thread.
3. Place the button where it needs to be sewn on the shirt.
4. Push the needle through the fabric and the buttonhole on the button.
5. Pull the thread tight to secure the button in place.
6. Push the needle through the fabric again, but this time a few millimeters away from the first hole.
7. Repeat steps 4-6 until you have gone around the button a few times.
8. Tie a knot at the end of the thread to secure the button.
9. Cut off any extra thread.
10. Your button is now sewn on the shirt!
output_2:
Sewing buttons onto clothing can be done with ease, as long as you have the right supplies and know what steps to take. Here are some tips for attaching a button to your garment: 
1. Gather all of your materials - thread, needle, scissors, pins, and the button itself. Make sure they're in good condition and ready to use.
2. Carefully unbutton the shirt or other item of clothing where you want to attach the button. Pull it away from the rest of the material so there’s enough space around the button to work.
3. Place the button at the desired spot and make sure it looks straight. Pin it into place if necessary.
4. Take one end of the thread and pass it through the hole of the button. Then bring the thread back up and tie a knot near the top of the button. This will securely hold the thread in place.
5. Insert the needle through both layers of fabric (the front side and the lining) just below the edge of the button. Pass the needle down about halfway between the two holes.
6. Come up again and insert the needle underneath the first stitches made. Continue making small stitches until the entire perimeter of the button has been secured.
7. Cut off any excess threads and tuck them inside the buttonhole. If needed, trim the ends of the thread close to the button.
8. Finally, carefully press the area around the button to ensure a neat finish.

instruction: How did serial killers get away with murder for so long in the 70s and 80s?
output_1: Serial killers in the 1970s and 1980s were able to get away with murder for a variety of reasons. First, forensic technology and investigative techniques were not as advanced as they are today, making it more difficult to catch criminals. Furthermore, law enforcement agencies were often understaffed and underfunded, resulting in a lack of resources to pursue investigations. Additionally, many serial killers were able to hide in plain sight, blending in with their communities and avoiding suspicion. Finally, serial killers were often geographically mobile, making it difficult for law enforcement to track them down.
output_2: In the 1970's and early 1980’s, there was a rise of notorious serial killers who were able to evade capture by law enforcement for extended periods of time due to various factors such as lack of technology or resources available at the time. This period saw some of the most infamous cases including The Zodiac Killer, Son of Sam, Jeffrey Dahmer, Ted Bundy, John Wayne Gacy, and David Berkowitz among others. These criminals often operated within their own communities, taking advantage of local knowledge and familiarity which allowed them to remain undetected for longer than they should have been. Additionally, many police forces had limited resources and technological capabilities during this era, making it difficult to track down these perpetrators quickly. Furthermore, some of these individuals used psychological manipulation tactics on victims and witnesses alike, further complicating investigations. In addition, some of these offenders were able to take advantage of legal loopholes or outdated laws which made prosecution more challenging. Finally, some of these crimes went unsolved due to a lack of public awareness about certain types of crime or because victims chose to keep quiet rather than report what happened to authorities. Ultimately, while some of these criminal acts may never be fully explained, it can be said that a combination of all of these factors contributed to why these serial killers got away with murder for so long.

instruction: How do I make apple juice?
output_1:
1. Wash and peel four to five apples.
2. Cut the apples into small pieces.
3. Place the apple pieces into a blender or food processor and blend until smooth.
4. Strain the blended apples through a fine mesh sieve or a cheesecloth to remove the pulp and seeds.
5. Pour the juice into a pot and heat it over medium-high heat, stirring often.
6. Once the juice has reached a light simmer, reduce the heat and simmer for an additional 10 minutes.
7. Allow the juice to cool before serving. Enjoy!
output_2: Making your own homemade apple juice requires only three simple steps and can be done in less than 30 minutes! First, wash and cut up about two pounds of apples into small pieces (about one-inch cubes). Place them in a large pot with enough water to cover the apples. Bring this mixture to a boil over high heat for five minutes or until the apples are softened. Then use a strainer to remove the solids from the liquid. Next, pour the filtered liquid through a cheese cloth or fine mesh sieve to further filter out any remaining particles. Finally, store the juice in an air tight container in the refrigerator for up to seven days. That's it - you now have freshly made apple juice ready to enjoy!

instruction: I like to host guests at my home from time to time, and I am gathering  recipes of different dishes and drinks to keep things interesting. I am interested in trying some Israeli dishes. Can you give me a recipe Israeli Cheese Bourekas?
output_1:
Ingredients:
-1/2 kg puff pastry
-2 eggs
-1/2 cup olive oil
-1/2 cup chopped parsley
-1/2 teaspoon black pepper
-1/4 teaspoon cumin
-250 grams feta cheese, crumbled
-250 grams grated cheese
-2 tablespoons grated onion

Instructions:

1. Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C).

2. In a bowl, whisk together eggs, olive oil, parsley, black pepper and cumin.

3. On a floured surface, roll out the puff pastry to a thickness of about 1/8 inch (3 mm).

4. Cut the pastry into circles about 4 inches (10 cm) in diameter.

5. Place a tablespoon of feta cheese and grated cheese in the center of each circle. Top with a tablespoon of the egg mixture and a teaspoon of grated onion.

6. Fold the circles in half and pinch the edges together to seal.

7. Place the bourekas on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.

8. Brush the top of each boureka with the remaining egg mixture and sprinkle with some extra grated cheese.

9. Bake for 20-25 minutes, until golden brown.

10. Serve warm. Enjoy!
output_2:
Ingredients (Makes about 12-15 boureka):
•	4 tablespoons olive oil
•	3 large eggs
•	½ teaspoon salt
•	¼ teaspoon ground black pepper
•	¾ cup all-purpose flour
•	1 cup grated cheddar cheese
•	1/3 cup chopped onion
•	1/3 cup chopped parsley
Instructions:
1. Preheat oven to 375°F. Grease a baking sheet with cooking spray or line it with parchment paper.
2. In a medium bowl, whisk together the oil, eggs, salt, and pepper until blended. Add the flour and stir until combined. Stir in the cheese, onions, and parsley until everything is evenly distributed.
3. Drop heaping tablespoonfuls of the mixture onto the prepared baking sheet. Bake for 20 minutes, or until golden brown. Serve warm.

instruction: How can I make bubble solution?

instruction: I like to host guests at my home from time to time, and I am gathering  recipes of different dishes and drinks to keep things interesting. I am interested in trying some Tunisian dishes. Can you give me a recipe Tunisian Kammounia?
output_1:
Tunisian Kammounia Recipe
Ingredients: 
-1/4 cup olive oil
-1 onion, chopped
-2 cloves garlic, minced
-1 teaspoon ground cumin
-1 teaspoon ground coriander
-1 teaspoon sweet paprika
-1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon
-1/4 teaspoon ground allspice
-1/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper
-1/3 cup chopped fresh parsley
-2 tablespoons chopped fresh mint
-1 (15-ounce) can chickpeas, rinsed and drained
-1 (14-ounce) can diced tomatoes
-1/2 cup vegetable broth
-Salt and freshly ground black pepper, to taste
-1/2 cup couscous
-1/4 cup toasted slivered almonds

Instructions:

1. Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add the onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, about 5 minutes. Add the garlic, cumin, coriander, paprika, cinnamon, allspice, and cayenne pepper and cook, stirring, until fragrant, about 1 minute.

2. Add the parsley, mint, chickpeas, tomatoes, and vegetable broth and season with salt and pepper. Bring to a boil, reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer for 20 minutes.

3. Meanwhile, bring 2 cups of water to a boil in a separate pot. Add the couscous, cover, and turn off the heat. Let sit for 5 minutes.

4. Fluff the couscous with a fork and stir into the stew. Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes. Sprinkle with the almonds before serving.
output_2:
Tunisian Kammouna (also known as Kamounak or Ghmous) is a traditional Tunisian dish made with potatoes, tomato sauce, onions, garlic, cumin, coriander, olive oil, and spices such as paprika and turmeric. It can be served either hot or cold. The ingredients are boiled until tender then mashed together for a creamy texture. This dish goes well with bread, salads, and other side dishes. Here's how to make it:
- Peel and cut two large potatoes into small cubes. Boil them in salted water until they are soft. Drain the water and set aside.
- Heat one tablespoon of olive oil in a pan over medium heat. Add three chopped onions and sauté until golden brown.
- Add four cloves of minced garlic and cook for another minute before adding five cups of crushed tomatoes. Simmer for about ten minutes.
- Stir in half teaspoon each of ground cumin, coriander, paprika, and turmeric. Cook for another few minutes.
- Add the potatoes and season with salt and pepper to taste. Continue simmering for fifteen more minutes. Serve warm or chilled. Enjoy!

instruction: I want to learn more about airplanes. How were they created?
output_1: The invention of the airplane is credited to two brothers, Orville and Wilbur Wright, who are often referred to as the Wright Brothers. The Wright Brothers flew the first powered airplane on December 17, 1903. The plane flew for 12 seconds and covered 120 feet. The brothers used a four-cylinder gasoline engine to power the aircraft. The engine was designed by Charles Taylor, a machinist who worked for the brothers. The Wright brothers continued to make improvements to their design, eventually creating a plane that could fly for more than 30 minutes.
output_2: Airplanes have been around for over 100 years, and their development has come in leaps and bounds since then. The first powered aircraft was invented by the Wright brothers in 1903, who used a lightweight engine with propellers attached to it. Since then, many different types of engines have been developed which allow planes to fly at higher altitudes and faster speeds than ever before. Modern day airplanes are made up of several components including wings, fuselage, tail fin, landing gear, cockpit, and engines. Each component plays its own role in helping the plane stay aloft while carrying passengers or cargo from one destination to another. Wings provide lift and stability, while the fuselage holds all the other parts together and provides space for passengers and crew members. Tail fins help steer the plane during flight, while landing gears support the weight of the plane when on the ground. Cockpits contain instruments and controls necessary for pilots to navigate the plane safely through the sky. Engines provide thrust and power to move the plane forward. All these components must work together harmoniously if the plane is to remain safe and efficient throughout its journey. With advancements in technology, modern-day airplanes can now travel much further distances than ever before, making them essential tools for transportation across long distances.

instruction: Can you tell me a very easy to way clean a showerhead?
output_1: To clean a showerhead, you can fill a plastic bag with white vinegar and tie it around the showerhead. Leave it overnight and in the morning, remove the bag and rinse the showerhead with warm water.
output_2:
Cleaning your shower head can be quick and simple, but it's important to do so regularly in order to keep water pressure high and prevent mold or mildew buildup. Here are some steps for how to clean a shower head: 
1. Turn off the water supply at the valve and disconnect the hose from the shower head.
2. Use a soft brush or pipe cleaner to remove any debris stuck inside of the nozzles. Be sure not to use too much force as this could damage the shower head.
3. Mix together one part white vinegar with nine parts warm water and pour into the reservoir. Let sit overnight before using again.
4. Rinse out the shower head by running the water through it until all traces of soap scum have been removed.
5. If necessary, scrub the outside of the shower head with baking soda and then rinse thoroughly.
6. Reattach the hose and turn on the water supply to check for leaks.

instruction: Please give me a list of planets in our solar system.  I am going to choose which one I want to know more.
output_1: The planets in our solar system are: Mercury, Venus, Earth, Mars, Jupiter, Saturn, Uranus, and Neptune.
output_2:
1. Mercury - The closest planet to the Sun, it has no atmosphere and temperatures on its surface can reach up to 800°F (427°C). It orbits the sun every 59 days.
2. Venus – This planet is much hotter than Mercury with temperatures reaching over 860°F (462°C) due to its thick atmosphere made mostly of carbon dioxide. Its orbit takes around 225 Earth days.
3. Earth – Our home planet, this is the only known place where life exists. With an average temperature of about 55 degrees Fahrenheit (12 Celsius), it’s the third-largest planet in terms of diameter but fourth when ranked by mass.
4. Mars – Known as “The Red Planet”, it's smaller than Earth but has a thinner atmosphere composed mainly of CO2. Temperature ranges from below freezing at night to above boiling during daytime. Orbital period is approximately 687 Earth days.
5. Jupiter – The largest planet in our Solar System, it has the most moons and an immense atmosphere consisting primarily of hydrogen and helium. Orbiting time is roughly 11 years.
6. Saturn – Another gas giant like Jupiter, it has rings made of ice particles and dust. Takes 10,759 Earth days for one revolution.
7. Uranus – A large, cold planet with extreme tilted axis and unique features such as its distinctive rings. Orbits take 84 Earth years.
8. Neptune – Farthest away from the Sun and coldest of all eight planets, it also has the strongest winds. Orbits last 165 Earth years.

instruction: Who was the first lead vocal for the rock band Starship?

The original lead singer of Starship, which later became known as simply "Starship", was Grace Slick. She joined the group in 1975 and remained with them until their breakup in 1986. During her time with the band she recorded several hit songs including “We Built This City”, “Sara” (a cover of The Hollies’ song), “Nothing's Gonna Stop Us Now,” and many more. After leaving Starship, Slick went on to have success with her solo career, releasing albums such as Manhole and Welcome To The Wrecking Ball! In addition to singing, Slick also wrote or co-wrote most of the material released by Starship during her tenure with the band.

In 1987, Slick left Starship and was replaced by Mickey Thomas who had previously been the frontman for the bands Autograph and Alien Project. With Thomas at the helm, Starship continued to release successful singles like “It’s Not Over Yet”, “Hold On” and “Laying Down My Life”. Despite having different singers, Starship managed to maintain its popularity throughout the late ‘80s and early ‘90s. However, after the death of keyboardist Paul Kantner in 2016, it appears that Starship has disbanded permanently.

instruction: Best way to defrost a refrigerator freezer?
output_1: The best way to defrost a refrigerator freezer is to first turn off the refrigerator and unplug it. Then take out all the food and store it in a cool place. Next, use a hairdryer or a towel soaked in hot water to heat up and melt the ice. Finally, wipe away the melted ice and dry the area before plugging the refrigerator back in and turning it on.
output_2: The best way to defrost a refrigerator freezer is to first unplug it from its power source and allow it to completely thaw out for at least 24 hours in order to prevent any food spoilage. Once the appliance has been unplugged, you can begin to manually defrost it by removing all of the shelves and packing materials inside so as not to damage them when they are removed. Then, use a hair dryer or similar device set on low heat to slowly warm up the interior walls of the freezer until the ice begins to melt. This process may take several days depending upon how large your freezer is. instruction: How do I know if my house has a water leak?
output_1:
To determine if your house has a water leak, look for the following signs: 
1. High water bills 
2. Wet or damp spots on walls, floors or ceilings 
3. Musty odors 
4. Visible signs of water damage, such as peeling paint or wallpaper 
5. Water pooling in your yard or foundation 
6. The sound of running water when all faucets are off 
7. Increased water meter readings when all water sources are off 
8. Mold or mildew growth
output_2:
If you suspect your home may have a water leak, there are several signs to look for and steps to take in order to confirm it. 
The first step is to check around your property for any visible signs of moisture or wet spots on the ground outside. If you see these, then this could be indicative of a larger issue inside your home such as a leaking pipe or faulty appliance. Additionally, checking your utility bills can help identify potential issues with high usage of water over a period of time which might indicate a leak somewhere within your plumbing system. You should also keep an eye out for mold growth near areas where water would typically accumulate like under sinks, behind walls, and in attics.

Another way to detect a possible water leak is by listening for unusual noises coming from pipes or fixtures. For example, if you hear running water when all faucets and showers are turned off, then this could mean that one of them has a small leak. Similarly, if you notice strange sounds emanating from your hot water heater, this could suggest that it needs repair due to a build-up of sediment or minerals.

Finally, you can use specialized equipment to detect hidden water leaks. A water detector will allow you to pinpoint exactly where the source of the problem lies so that you can make necessary repairs quickly. It works by sending out sound waves through the wall and listening for echoes caused by air pockets trapped between the wall and the pipe. This method is especially useful for locating leaks behind walls or beneath floors.

Overall, keeping an eye out for visible signs of water damage, listening for odd noises, and using specialized tools can help you determine whether or not your home has a water leak.

instruction: I like to host guests at my home from time to time, and I am gathering  recipes of different dishes and drinks to keep things interesting. I am interested in trying some Uruguayan dishes. Can you give me a recipe for Vitel toné?
output_1:
Vitel Toné Recipe

Ingredients:
- 2 boiled eggs
- 2 cooked, thinly sliced veal cutlets
- 1/2 cup of mayonnaise
- 2 tablespoons of capers
- 1 tablespoon of Dijon mustard
- 2 tablespoons of olive oil
- 1/4 cup of white wine vinegar
- Salt and pepper to taste
- 2 tablespoons of chopped parsley

Instructions:

1. Place the sliced veal cutlets in a shallow dish.

2. In a separate bowl, mix the mayonnaise, capers, mustard, olive oil, white wine vinegar, salt and pepper.

3. Spread the mayonnaise mixture over the veal cutlets, making sure each cutlet is well-coated.

4. Place the boiled eggs on top of the veal cutlets, and top with the chopped parsley.

5. Serve chilled, and enjoy!
output_2:
Vitel Toné (also known as Vitello Tonnato) is a classic Italian dish made with veal cutlets, tuna, capers, mayonnaise, and a hint of orange juice or zest. It originated in Genoa, Italy but has since become popular all over Europe and South America. The name literally translates to “veal and tuna” in Italian. This light yet flavorful dish can be served either hot or cold. Here’s how it's done!
Ingredients:
-4 veal cutlets
-2 tablespoons olive oil
-1/3 cup white wine
-1 teaspoon salt
-1/2 teaspoon black pepper
-6 slices of tuna
-2 cloves garlic, minced
-Juice of one lemon
-Capers, drained
-Mayonnaise
Instructions:
1. Preheat your oven to 375°F.
2. In a large bowl, combine the veal cutlets, olive oil, white wine, salt, and pepper. Mix until everything is evenly coated. Place the mixture on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.
3. Bake the veal for about 8 minutes per side, flipping halfway through. Remove from heat when cooked through. Let cool before cutting into thin strips.
4. Meanwhile, prepare the sauce by combining the tuna, garlic, lemon juice, and capers in a small bowl. Slowly whisk in the mayo until fully incorporated. Set aside.
5. To assemble the dish, place two pieces of the veal onto each plate. Top with the tuna mixture and drizzle with the orange sauce. Sprinkle with additional capers if desired. Serve chilled. Enjoy!

instruction: I like to host guests at my home from time to time, and I am gathering  recipes of different dishes and drinks to keep things interesting. I am interested in trying some Indonesian dishes. Can you give me a recipe for Opor Ayam?
output_1:
Opor Ayam Recipe
Ingredients: 
• 1 whole chicken, cut into 8 pieces
• 5 shallots, finely chopped
• 2 cloves garlic, peeled and finely chopped
• 2 stalks lemongrass, finely chopped
• 2-3 red chillies, finely chopped
• 2 tablespoons of vegetable oil
• 2-3 tablespoons of ground coriander
• 1 teaspoon ground turmeric
• 1 teaspoon ground cumin
• 2 tablespoons tamarind concentrate
• 2 tablespoons palm sugar or brown sugar
• Salt to taste
• ½ cup coconut milk
• 1 cup water
• 2 bay leaves
• 2-3 kaffir lime leaves

Instructions:
1. Heat the oil in a large pan over medium heat, then add the shallots, garlic and lemongrass. Cook until the shallots are soft and fragrant.
2. Add the chillies, ground coriander, turmeric and cumin and stir to combine.
3. Add the chicken and stir to coat with the spices.
4. Add the tamarind concentrate, palm sugar, salt, coconut milk, water, bay leaves and kaffir lime leaves. Stir to combine.
5. Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat to low and cover the pan. Simmer for about 20 minutes, until the chicken is cooked through.
6. Serve the Opor Ayam with steamed white rice. Enjoy!
output_2: Opor ayam (chicken porridge) is one of the most popular traditional Indonesian dishes. It's made with chunks of steamed or boiled chicken cooked in a savory broth flavored with spices such as coriander, cumin, turmeric, ginger, galangal, and lemongrass. The broth can be thickened with rice flour or tapioca starch. To make it even more delicious, add vegetables such as potatoes, carrots, onions, and tomato wedges. Serve this comfort food hot with a side of steamed white rice and sambal. Enjoy!

instruction: What do the different octane values of gasoline mean?
output_1: Octane values are a measure of the fuel's performance and determine its ability to resist knocking or pinging during combustion. Higher octane fuels have more resistance to knocking or pinging, which allows the engine to run more efficiently and with greater power output. Lower octane fuels burn more quickly, which can cause engine knock or pinging.
output_2:
The octane rating of gasoline indicates its resistance to engine knocking and pinging, which can be caused by spark-ignited engines when they are running on fuel with too low a Research Octane Number (RON). The higher the RON number, the more resistant it will be to engine knocking and pinging. 

Octane ratings range from 87 to 100, with lower numbers indicating lesser resistance to engine knocking and pinging. Generally speaking, regular grade unleaded gasoline has an octane rating between 87 and 93; midgrade grades have an octane rating between 93 and 96; and premium grades have an octane rating above 96. High performance vehicles may require a higher octane rated fuel than what is recommended for normal driving conditions in order to prevent engine knocking or pinging. 

In addition to octane ratings, there are other factors such as temperature, altitude, and air quality that affect how well a particular type of gasoline performs in an engine. For example, cold weather can reduce the efficiency of some types of fuels while hotter temperatures can increase their effectiveness. Additionally, certain additives used in gasolines can help improve combustion at high altitudes where atmospheric pressure is reduced.

instruction: How can I fix a leaking roof?
output_1:
1. Inspect the roof for the source of the leak. Look for areas where the shingles or tiles have become loose or displaced and repair any damaged areas.
2. Patch any holes or cracks in the roof with roofing cement or caulk.
3. Apply roofing tar to the area around the leak.
4. Place a piece of sheet metal over the patched area.
5. Apply roofing cement around the edges of the sheet metal.
6. Place a layer of roofing felt over the metal.
7. Apply shingles or tiles on top of the roofing felt.
8. Seal the edges of the shingles or tiles with roofing cement.
9. Check the area for any further leaks.
output_2:
Fixing a leaky roof requires some basic knowledge of home repair and an understanding of how different types of roofs are constructed. The first step in fixing any type of roof leak is to identify where it’s coming from, which involves using a flashlight at night or wearing a pair of binoculars during the day to look for signs of water damage on the ceiling below. Once you have identified the source of the leak, you need to determine what kind of material is causing the problem – whether it's shingles, tiles, metal panels, etc. 
Once you know what materials make up your roof, you will be able to decide which method of repair is best suited for your situation. For example, if the leak is caused by missing shingles, then replacing them would be the most effective solution; however, if the leak is due to a faulty seal around a skylight, then you may want to consider replacing the entire unit instead. Additionally, depending on the severity of the leak, you might also need to replace the underlying decking boards as well.
Finally, once all repairs have been made, it is important to inspect the area again to ensure there are no further issues with the roof. This should include checking for loose shingles, damaged flashings, and other potential problems before they become major headaches down the line.

instruction: I have a hard time falling asleep.  Is there any type of music that can help me fall asleep faster?

Studies suggest that slow-paced instrumental or calming music with low volumes can reduce stress levels and promote relaxation. Music without lyrics has been found to be particularly effective for this purpose because it does not contain distracting elements such as words which could cause your mind to wander. Additionally, some people find that listening to nature sounds like ocean waves or rain can also help them to relax their minds and bodies enough to drift off into dreamland.

If you are looking for specific genres of music to try out, here are some suggestions:
1. Classical music – This genre often contains slower tempos and soothing melodies that can help calm the body and mind.
2. Ambient/New Age music – These styles of music usually feature soft instruments and peaceful soundscapes that create a tranquil atmosphere.
3. Relaxing jazz – Jazz typically features upbeat rhythms but many artists have released albums featuring mellow tunes perfect for unwinding before bedtime.
4. Meditation music – This style of music generally consists of repetitive chants and gentle instrumentals designed to encourage deep breathing and inner reflection.
5. Spa music – Soft, light instrumentals combined with calming vocals make spa music ideal for creating a serene environment conducive to rest.

instruction: Hi, I've decided to keep a rat as a pet. How do I house, feed, and otherwise care for it?
output_1:
To house and feed your rat, you'll need to provide a safe, comfortable, and clean environment. You can purchase a rat cage with a secure lid, bedding, and chew toys to keep your rat entertained. Make sure to provide fresh, clean water every day and a balanced diet of high-quality rat food. 

It's also important to handle your rat regularly to help it become socialized and comfortable around people. Pet your rat gently and play with it for a few minutes each day. Additionally, take your rat to the vet once a year for a check-up and to make sure it's healthy. 

Finally, make sure to keep your rat's cage and environment clean. Clean the cage once a week and replace the bedding every few weeks. Finally, keep an eye out for signs of illness like sneezing, weight loss, or aggressive behavior.
output_2:
Congratulations on your decision to get a rat! Rats make great pets and can provide years of companionship if you take proper steps in their housing, nutrition, and healthcare. 

Housing: Rats need a secure home with plenty of space to roam around and explore. A large aquarium or plastic storage container will work well. Make sure there are enough ventilation holes so air can circulate and prevent respiratory illnesses. The floor should be lined with paper towels or newspaper to help reduce odors and keep the area clean. Provide them with bedding such as shredded paper or wood chips which they can use to build nests. Place some food-grade safe items like wooden blocks or cardboard boxes in the cage for them to play with.
Feeding: Rats require a balanced diet consisting of grains (such as oatmeal), fruits & vegetables, protein sources (like eggs or small bits of cooked meat) and supplements (such as vitamin C). Feed them twice daily and remove any uneaten food after 15 minutes. You may also want to offer treats like fresh fruit or vegetable pieces once per day.
Health Care: Regularly check your rats’ fur for fleas, ticks, and other parasites. Brush their teeth regularly using a vet-approved dental solution to avoid periodontal disease. Check their ears weekly for signs of mites, redness, or discharge. Finally, have regular veterinary exams to ensure good overall health.

instruction: How do you get water in the desert?
output_1: In the desert, you can get water by collecting dew, harvesting rainwater, using a solar still, or finding a water source such as a spring or oasis.
output_2:
Water can be found in many places in the desert, but it often requires some effort to access it. The most common way of getting water from the desert environment is by collecting rainwater or groundwater through wells and other methods. Rainfall provides the majority of fresh water available in arid regions, so capturing this resource is key for survival. 
Another method of obtaining water from the desert is by utilizing evaporation ponds. These are man-made bodies of water designed to capture moisture from the air and concentrate it into usable sources of drinking water. This process works best when there is plenty of sunshine and little wind, as these conditions help create favorable conditons for evaporative cooling. Evaporation pond systems require regular maintenance and monitoring to ensure they remain effective at gathering water.
Collecting dew from plants and grasses is another way people have been able to find water in dry areas. Dew forms on leaves during nighttime hours due to the combination of heat and humidity, which makes them excellent sources of hydration. Additionally, fog harvesting has become increasingly popular among those living in arid climates. Fog collectors use specialized equipment to trap droplets of water from nearby mountains and bring them down to lower elevations where they can be used for irrigating crops or providing potable water.
Finally, desalination techniques allow humans to extract salt and minerals from sea water, making it possible to convert ocean water into clean, safe drinking water. Desalinization processes involve multiple steps such as reverse osmosis, distillation, and electrodialysis, all of which must work together to produce large amounts of pure H2O.

instruction: How do I get better at aiming with my slingshot?

4. Adjust the rubber bands: Make sure the rubber bands are adjusted properly for your slingshot. If they are too tight or too loose, they can affect the accuracy of your shots.
5. Use the right ammo: Choose the right ammo for your slingshot such as marbles or steel balls. This will help you achieve better accuracy and distance with your shots.

2. Practice by shooting small objects like stones or pebbles into targets such as cans or paper plates. This will help you develop muscle memory for accurate shots.

instruction: I like to host guests at my home from time to time, and I am gathering  recipes of different dishes and drinks to keep things interesting. I am interested in trying some Argentinian dishes. Can you give me a recipe for Milanesa de peceto?
output_1:
Milanesa de peceto Recipe 
Ingredients: 
-1 lb. boneless veal cutlets 
-1 cup all-purpose flour 
-2 large eggs 
-1/4 cup breadcrumbs 
-1 teaspoon salt 
-1 teaspoon black pepper 
-1/4 cup olive oil 

Instructions: 
1. Place the veal cutlets between two pieces of wax paper and lightly pound them with a meat mallet to about 1/4 inch thickness. 

2. In a shallow bowl, combine the flour, salt, and pepper. 

3. In a separate shallow bowl, whisk together the eggs. 

4. In a third shallow bowl, mix together the breadcrumbs. 

5. Dip the veal cutlets in the flour mixture, then into the eggs, and then into the breadcrumbs. 

6. Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. 

7. Add the veal cutlets to the hot oil. Cook until golden brown and cooked through, about 3-4 minutes per side. 

8. Transfer the milanesa de peceto to a plate lined with paper towels to absorb any excess oil. 

9. Serve warm with a side of mashed potatoes or a salad. Enjoy!
output_2:
Milanesa de Peceto (Argentine-style Breaded Chicken Cutlet)
Ingredients:
• 4 boneless chicken breasts, cut into thin strips
• 2 tablespoons olive oil
• Salt & pepper, to taste
• 1 egg, beaten
• ½ cup all-purpose flour
• ¼ teaspoon garlic powder
• ¼ teaspoon paprika
• ¼ teaspoon cumin
• 3 slices white bread, crust removed
Instructions:
1. In a shallow bowl, combine the olive oil with salt and pepper; add the chicken strips and toss until evenly coated. Set aside.
2. Beat together the egg and 1 tablespoon water in another shallow bowl. Add the flour and seasonings; mix well. Dip each piece of chicken into the egg mixture then coat it thoroughly with the flour mixture. Place on a plate or tray.
3. Heat the vegetable oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Fry the chicken pieces in batches until golden brown, about 5 minutes per side. Remove the fried chicken onto paper towels to absorb excess grease. Serve hot.

instruction: I have my grandfather's antique fountain pen and a bottle of ink, but have never done this before. Can you tell me how to refill the fountain pen?
output_1:
1. Begin by uncapping the fountain pen and removing the ink cartridge.
2. Fill the ink bottle with a compatible fountain pen ink.
3. Dip the nib of the fountain pen into the bottle of ink. Make sure that the nib is completely submerged. 
4. Gently roll the nib to remove excess ink.
5. Reinsert the ink cartridge into the fountain pen and replace the cap.
6. Test the fountain pen by writing on a piece of paper.
output_2:
1. Uncap your fountain pen and remove any old ink from the nib by wiping it with a cloth or paper towel. 
2. Filling the reservoir on top of the pen with clean water will allow for more ink to be drawn up into the feed when writing. 
3. Place some ink drops onto a piece of paper and then use another piece of paper to blot them up until they are completely absorbed. This should leave a thin layer of ink atop the surface of the paper. 
4. Insert the nib of the pen into the opening of the bottle of ink and hold it there for several seconds while allowing the ink to flow through the feeder and into the barrel of the pen. 
5. Once all of the ink has been transferred, unplug the pen from the ink source and cap the end of the pen. 
6. To ensure that no air bubbles remain inside the pen, write something on a sheet of paper using the new ink. If any bubbles appear, repeat steps two through five until the ink flows smoothly without any bubbles.

instruction: Hi, I'd like to play ice hockey. Can you explain how the game works?
output_1: Sure! Ice hockey is a team sport played on ice. It is usually played between two teams of six players each, but can also be played with fewer players. The objective of the game is to score goals by shooting a hard rubber puck into the opposing team's net. Players attempt to control the puck using a hockey stick and can pass it to teammates or take shots at the goal. The team with the most goals at the end of the game wins.
output_2:
Ice hockey is a fast-paced and exciting sport played on a large sheet of ice with two teams of six players each attempting to score into a net defended by the opposing team. The objective of the game is for one team to score more goals than their opponent within a set time limit or number of rounds. 
The game begins when both teams line up in front of their respective nets and drop the puck between them. Players can use any part of their bodies (including sticks) to pass or shoot the puck towards the goal. When a player has possession of the puck they must keep it in sight at all times as it cannot be passed backward. If a player loses control of the puck while it is still in the offensive zone, then the other team will gain possession. 
When a player shoots the puck past the goaltender and into the net, this counts as a goal. Goals are worth one point and assists are also awarded to players who help create scoring opportunities. A tie game after regulation time ends results in overtime where the first team to score wins. In some cases, if neither team scores during overtime, a penalty shot may take place which only involves one player from either team taking a shot against the opposite goalie.

instruction: What is kevlar made out of?
output_1: Kevlar is made out of poly-paraphenylene terephthalamide, a type of synthetic fiber.
output_2: Kevlar, also known as para-aramid fiber, is a synthetic polymer composed of interlocked molecules of para-phenylenediamine (PPD). It was developed by DuPont in 1965 and first used commercially to make bulletproof vests for police officers. Kevlar is five times stronger than steel but lightweight and flexible. Its high strength-to-weight ratio makes it ideal for use in products such as ropes, cables, fabrics, and composites. In addition to its uses in protective gear, Kevlar has been incorporated into many other applications including medical devices, automotive parts, sporting goods, and more. The material can be woven or knitted together with other fibers like nylon or polyester to create composite materials which are strong yet light weight. These composite materials have found their way into everything from bicycle frames to spacecrafts.

instruction: Hi, I'd like to learn how to play racquetball. Can you explain the game to me?
output_1: Sure! Racquetball is a sport that is played with four walls, a racquet, and a ball. The object of the game is to hit the ball with your racquet and make it bounce off of the walls without your opponent hitting it back. You can only hit the ball once before your opponent has to hit it back. The first person to reach 11 points wins the game.
output_2:
Racquetball is a fun and exciting sport played with two or four players on a court similar in size to a badminton court. The goal of the game is for each player to hit a small rubber ball against the walls of their opponent’s court using any part of their bodies except their hands or rackets. 
The serve begins by one player hitting the ball off the back wall into the opposite service box at least six feet away from the front wall. After this initial shot, points are scored when either player hits the ball so it bounces once on the floor and then hits the front wall above the top of the service line. Each point ends when a player fails to return the ball within the allotted time limit (25 seconds). When a player wins seven points they win a game; if both players reach seven games, the winner will be determined by who has won more games. 
In addition to basic rules, there are also several variations of Racquetball such as “cutthroat” which requires only three players instead of four, and “champions” where the first person to score ten points wins the match. There are many different strategies used during matches including aggressive shots near the front wall, defensive shots aimed towards the sidewalls, and lobs over your opponents head. With its fast-paced action and unique strategy, Racquetball is sure to provide hours of entertainment!

instruction: When were smart phones first made?
output_1: The first smartphone was the IBM Simon, which was released in 1994.
output_2: Smartphones have been around since 1992, when IBM released its Simon Personal Communicator device. It was one of the earliest devices to feature a touchscreen and had many features similar to modern-day smartphones such as email access, calendar, address book, calculator, alarm clock, and even a game called "Soda Blast". The phone also featured a two-way pager system which allowed users to send messages back and forth with other people who owned Simons. However, it wasn't until 1996 that the world saw another major breakthrough in mobile technology - the Ericsson T300. This device was the first ever GSM (Global System for Mobile communications) phone and ushered in a new era of international cellular communication. In addition to being able to make calls, this device could store contacts, play games, take pictures, and even surf the web using WAP (Wireless Application Protocol). Since then, numerous advancements have been made in terms of both hardware and software capabilities, leading up to today’s high-end smartphone models. Smartphones are now capable of doing almost anything you can do on your computer including streaming movies, playing video games, taking photos/videos, sending emails, browsing the internet, making payments, and much more.

instruction: Hi, I'd like to learn to bake challah. Can you give me a recipe for that?
output_1:
Ingredients:
- 3/4 cup warm water
- 1/3 cup sugar
- 2 1/4 teaspoons active dry yeast
- 2 large eggs
- 1/4 cup vegetable oil
- 1 teaspoon salt
- 4 1/2 cups all-purpose flour
- 1 large egg yolk
- 1 tablespoon water

Instructions:
1. In a large bowl, combine warm water, sugar, and yeast. Let stand for 5 minutes until foamy.
2. Whisk in eggs, oil, and salt until combined.
3. Gradually add the flour, stirring until a soft dough forms.
4. Knead the dough on a lightly floured surface for about 10 minutes, until the dough is smooth and elastic.
5. Place the dough in a greased bowl, cover with a damp towel, and let it rise for 1 hour, or until doubled in size.
6. Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).
7. Punch down the dough and divide it into 3 equal pieces. Roll each piece into a long rope, about 18 inches long.
8. Braid the ropes together and place on a greased baking sheet.
9. In a small bowl, combine the egg yolk and 1 tablespoon of water. Brush the mixture on top of the challah.
10. Bake for 25 minutes, or until golden brown. Let cool before serving.
output_2:
Ingredients (Makes 2 large loaves):
- 4 cups all purpose flour
- 1 teaspoon salt
- 3/4 cup warm water
- 2 tablespoons sugar
- 2 tablespoons vegetable oil
- 1 package active dry yeast
- 1 egg
Instructions:
1. In a medium bowl, mix together the flour and salt. Add in the warm water and stir until it forms a smooth dough. Knead on a lightly floured surface for about five minutes. Place the dough into a greased bowl, cover with plastic wrap, and let rise in a warm place for one hour or until doubled in size.
2. Punch down the dough and divide it into two equal pieces. Roll each piece out onto a lightly floured surface into a long oval shape. Brush both sides of the ovals with the sugar and oil mixture. Sprinkle each side with the packet of active dry yeast. Spread the egg over the top of each roll. Cover with plastic wrap and let rise again for another thirty minutes.
3. Preheat your oven to 375 degrees Fahrenheit. Bake the bread for twenty minutes or until golden brown. Let cool before slicing. Enjoy!

instruction: Did Facebook corporation change its name?

In 2005, it dropped “the” from its official name to become simply “Facebook”. Since then, there have been no further changes or updates to their legal name. instruction: I like to host guests at my home from time to time, and I am gathering  recipes of different dishes and drinks to keep things interesting. I am interested in trying some Hong Kong  dishes. Can you give me a recipe for Tong Sui?
output_1:
Tong Sui Recipe
Ingredients:
- 1/2 cup of glutinous rice
- 2/3 cup of sugar
- 2 cups of water
- 2 tablespoons of sesame oil
- 1 tablespoon of chopped dried figs
- 2 tablespoons of dried red dates
- 2 tablespoons of chopped walnuts
- 2 tablespoons of chopped almonds
- 2 tablespoons of chopped peanuts
- 2 tablespoons of mung beans
- 2 tablespoons of osmanthus flowers
Instructions:
1. Rinse the glutinous rice and drain.
2. Place the glutinous rice into a pot with 2 cups of water.
3. Bring the pot to a boil over medium heat, then reduce the heat to low and simmer for 15 minutes.
4. Add the sugar and stir until it is completely dissolved.
5. Increase the heat to medium and stir in the sesame oil, dried figs, dried red dates, walnuts, almonds, peanuts, mung beans, and osmanthus flowers.
6. Cook for another 5 minutes until the ingredients are well combined.
7. Serve warm. Enjoy!
output_2: Tong Sui (农水) is a traditional Chinese New Year dessert made with glutinous rice flour, sugar, water, and malted milk powder. It has a sticky texture similar to tapioca pudding and a sweet flavor. The ingredients are boiled together until it reaches the desired consistency. This dessert can be served warm or cold. To make this delicious treat, start by combining one cup of glutinous rice flour, two tablespoons of white sugar, three cups of water, and one teaspoon of malted milk powder into a large pot over medium heat. Stir continuously as the mixture cooks and thickens. Once done, remove the pot from the stove and let cool before serving. Enjoy!

instruction: I want to start saving some money by growing my own food. Can I do this during the winter with an indoor garden?
output_1: Yes, you can grow your own food indoors during the winter with an indoor garden. An indoor garden can be set up with a hydroponic system, or with containers, shelves, and lighting. You will need soil, seeds, and some basic gardening tools to get started. Additionally, you may need to purchase grow lights if you don't have enough natural sunlight coming in.
output_2:
Yes, you can grow your own food even in the winter months using an indoor garden! There are several options for creating an indoor garden including hydroponic systems and soil-based gardens. Hydroponics uses water instead of soil as a medium for plant growth while soil-based gardens use potting mix or other types of soil. 
Hydroponic systems offer many advantages such as being able to control nutrient levels more precisely than with soil-based gardens, allowing for faster harvests, and requiring less space. They also require minimal maintenance since there’s no need to worry about weeds or soil fertility issues. However, they tend to be more expensive upfront compared to soil-based gardens. 
Soil-based gardens allow for greater flexibility when it comes to choosing plants and varieties, but may take longer to produce results due to slower root development. Soil-based gardens also have lower initial costs and typically don't require any additional equipment besides containers and lighting if needed. 
No matter which type of system you choose, make sure to provide adequate lighting (either natural sunlight or artificial) and maintain consistent temperatures between 65°F -70°F throughout the day and night. Additionally, ensure proper drainage and aeration by providing sufficient holes in the bottom of each container. Finally, keep an eye on pest populations and adjust accordingly. With these tips in mind, you should be well on your way to successfully growing your own food year round!

instruction: Is human blood ever any color other than red?
output_1: No, human blood is always red.
output_2:
Yes, human blood can be any number of colors besides red depending on what type of hemoglobin it contains and how much oxygen is present in the body at the time of testing. For example, if someone has sickle cell disease or thalassemia, their blood may appear to have a greenish tinge due to the presence of abnormal forms of hemoglobin. In rare cases, people with hereditary persistence of fetal hemoglobin (HPFH) may also have blue-colored blood because this form of hemoglobin does not absorb light as well as normal adult hemoglobin. Additionally, individuals who are suffering from severe anemias caused by iron deficiency or excessive bleeding may have pale pink or even white colored blood. 
In some instances, certain medications such as warfarin can cause changes in the color of one's blood. Warfarin causes the breakdown of clots which results in less oxygen being carried around the body, thus making the blood look bluish or grayish. Other drugs like aspirin and ibuprofen can make the blood appear yellow or orange. Finally, certain medical conditions such as liver diseases can affect the amount of bilirubin in the body, resulting in brownish or yellowish discoloration of the blood.

instruction: Please tell me about pearls.  Where are they found?
output_1: Pearls are a type of gemstone that are produced by mollusks, most often oysters. They are formed when a grain of sand or other irritant gets inside the mollusk and the mollusk secretes layers of calcium carbonate around it in order to protect itself. The result is a beautiful gemstone with a unique iridescence. Pearls are found all over the world, but the most valuable pearls come from the South Pacific and the Persian Gulf.
output_2: Pearls are organic gems formed in certain mollusks when layers of calcium carbonate crystals form around a foreign object, such as a grain of sand or parasite. They can be found in various oceans and seas throughout the world including the Persian Gulf, Red Sea, Indian Ocean, South China Sea, Japan, Australia, New Zealand, and the United States (Gulf of Mexico). Pearls have been highly sought after for centuries due to their luster, beauty, rarity, and value. The most valuable type of natural pearl is known as “south sea” pearls which come from the waters off the coast of Indonesia, the Philippines, and northern Australia. Cultured pearls, on the other hand, are grown using human intervention and are much more affordable than natural pearls. These cultured pearls can also be found in many different locations all over the world. In addition to being used in jewelry, pearls have also been used medicinally to treat everything from insomnia to heart disease.

instruction: What are some herbs I can dry out?
output_1:
Some herbs you can dry out include:

- Oregano
- Thyme
- Parsley
- Basil
- Rosemary
- Sage
- Lavender
- Mint
- Dill
- Marjoram
output_2:
1. Basil – This fragrant herb has many culinary uses and can be dried quickly by spreading it on a baking sheet in a single layer, then placing it in a warm area away from direct sunlight for 2-3 days until fully dried.
2. Thyme – Place thyme sprigs onto a clean tea towel or paper towels and roll up tightly before hanging them upside down in a cool, dark place for two weeks. Once completely dry, store in an air-tight container.
3. Oregano – Spread oregano leaves on a tray lined with parchment paper and leave in a warm spot for three days. Then transfer to a jar and seal tightly. Store in a cool, dark location.
4. Rosemary – Lay rosemary branches on a wire rack over a cookie sheet and put in a preheated oven at 150°F (65°C) for four hours. Remove from heat and let stand for another four hours. Transfer to an airtight container and keep refrigerated.
5. Sage – Hang sage leaves in small bunches in a warm, dry place for one week. Shake occasionally and remove any dust or insects. Store in an airtight container in a cool, dark place.
6. Mint – Gather mint leaves into a bundle and hang in a cool, dark place for several weeks. Unwrap the leaves when ready to use.
7. Parsley – Spread parsley leaves on a tray lined with parchment paper and leave in a warm spot for three days. Transfer to a jar and seal tightly. Keep stored in a cool, dark location.

instruction: I like to host guests at my home from time to time, and I am gathering  recipes of different dishes and drinks to keep things interesting. I am interested in trying some Indonesian dishes. Can you give me a recipe for Tahu Gejrot Cirebon?
output_1:

- 2 tablespoons of vinegar

- 1 tablespoon of ground ginger 
- 2 tablespoons of vegetable oil 
- 2 cloves of garlic, minced 
- 1/4 teaspoon of ground pepper 
- 1/2 teaspoon of ground cumin 
- 1/4 teaspoon of ground nutmeg

- 2 tablespoons of chopped scallions
- 2 tablespoons of chopped celery
- 2 tablespoons of chopped chilies

output_2:
Tahu Gejrot Cirebon (Fried Tofu with Chili Sauce)
Ingredients:

instruction: Whats the largest star in our galaxy?
output_1: The largest star in our galaxy is UY Scuti, a hypergiant located in the constellation Scutum. It has an estimated radius of 1,708 times that of the Sun's.
output_2:
The largest known star in our Galaxy, and one of the most massive stars ever discovered, is VY Canis Majoris (VY CMa). It has a mass around 50-60 times greater than the Sun's and its radius is estimated to be about 1200 times larger than the Sun’s. This means it radiates more energy than a million Suns! The star was first observed in 1901 when it suddenly became much brighter for several weeks before fading away again over the course of two years. Since then, astronomers have been studying this incredible object as it continues to evolve. Its current luminosity is approximately 3 million solar luminosities. 
Another large star found within our Milky Way is Rigel Kentaurus or "Rigel Kent", which is located near the center of the constellation of Orion. With a mass between 70 and 80 Solar masses, it is among the top five most massive stars currently known. It also has a very high surface temperature of up to 40,000K, making it one of the hottest stars in the Universe. Despite being so bright, Rigel Kent can only be seen with powerful telescopes due to its distance from Earth.  
Other notable large stars include Eta Carinae, which is thought to be one of the most massive stars in the Galaxy; and IRC+10216, which is a carbon-rich red giant star surrounded by dust and gas.

instruction: I'm trying to draw out a hopscotch game on my driveway. Can you walk me through how to do that?
output_1:
1. Start by drawing a square with chalk. Make sure it's big enough for the game. 
2. Divide the square into nine equal sections. 
3. Make two parallel lines in the middle of the square and draw a circle in the center. 
4. Number the nine sections, starting from the top left corner and going around clockwise. 
5. Draw a start line outside the left side of the square and a finish line outside the right side. 
6. Draw diagonal lines connecting the first and fourth squares, and the fourth and seventh squares. 
7. Draw a series of small squares around the outside of the game, connected to one another. 
8. Draw four short lines between the fifth and eighth squares. 
9. Draw two short lines in the middle of the square. 
10. Draw two small circles in the center of the square. 
11. Finally, draw two arrows pointing to the start and finish lines.
output_2:
1. Start by drawing two large squares, one slightly larger than the other, in your driveway. 
2. Draw four smaller squares inside each of these bigger ones and connect them with lines so they form a grid pattern. 
3. Divide this square into six equal sections using more lines. 
4. In each section, draw a circle or oval about three inches across. These will be the “hops.” 
5. Connect the hops together with curved lines to create paths from one end of the board to the other. The path should start at the bottom left corner of the big square and finish at the top right corner. 
6. At either end of the board, add a single circle for the "shooting space." This circle should be about five inches wide.  
7. Finally, color in all the shapes and make sure there are no gaps between any of the lines. Your hopscotch court is now ready!

instruction: Can you tell me how to make chocolate chip cookies?

3. Beat in the eggs, one at a time, then stir in the vanilla.
4. In a separate bowl, sift together the flour, baking soda, and salt; stir into the creamed mixture.

instruction: Where is Indonesia?
output_1: Indonesia is located in Southeast Asia.
output_2: Indonesia is located in Southeast Asia and consists of 17,508 islands stretching along the equator for over 5,200 kilometers (3,200 miles). It lies between the Indian Ocean and the Pacific Ocean, bordered by Malaysia to the north, Papua New Guinea to the east, Australia to the south and the Philippines to the west. Its capital city is Jakarta and its largest city is Surabaya. The official language is Bahasa Indonesia but there are many regional languages as well. Indonesia has a population of around 269 million people making it one of the most populous countries in the world. Islam is the predominant religion with Christianity being the second-largest faith. Indonesian culture is influenced by Hinduism, Buddhism, Confucianism and other religions from China and India. Indonesia's economy relies heavily on agriculture, minerals and tourism. Some popular destinations include Bali, Yogyakarta, Borobudur Temple, Komodo Islands and Mount Merapi.

instruction: Hi, I need to find the area of a 20 sided die for my math homework. Can you help me do that?
output_1:
Sure, I can help! The area of a 20-sided die is calculated by taking the surface area of a regular 20-sided polygon and dividing it by 2. The surface area of a regular 20-sided polygon is equal to 20 times the apothem times the perimeter of the polygon. The apothem of a regular 20-sided polygon is equal to the radius of the circumscribed circle divided by the cosine of 180 degrees divided by the number of sides. The radius of the circumscribed circle is equal to the side length of the die divided by 2 times the sine of 180 degrees divided by the number of sides. 

Therefore, the area of a 20-sided die is equal to (20 * (side length/2 * sine(180/20)) * (side length/2 * cosine(180/20))) / 2.
output_2: The area of a d20 (a twenty-sided dice) can be calculated by multiplying its length (each side of the die) by itself twice and then adding all those products together. The length of each side of a d20 is 1 inch long so if we multiply this number by itself two times it will give us 4 inches squared which when added with other four numbers gives us the total area of the die as 8 square inches. Therefore, the area of a d20 is 8 square inches.

instruction: I'm trying to learn how to install window blinds.

instruction: I want to learn more about becoming a CPA. How long does it take to become a CPA?
output_1: Generally, it takes between 150 to 180 credit hours to become a Certified Public Accountant (CPA). Most states require at least 150 credit hours, and some require up to 180 credit hours. Depending on the state, you may also need to complete additional educational courses or internships. Additionally, all states require CPA candidates to pass the Uniform CPA Exam. The exam is a four-part exam, and most people take between six months to two years to pass all four parts.
output_2:
Becoming a Certified Public Accountant (CPA) requires a combination of education, experience and examination. The process typically takes three years or longer depending on your educational background and work experience. 
The first step in becoming a CPA is to obtain a bachelor's degree from an accredited college or university with at least 150 semester hours of study including accounting courses such as auditing, taxation, financial reporting and management accounting. You must also complete a certain number of credit hours in business-related subjects like economics, finance and marketing. After you have completed these requirements, you can apply for admission to one of the state boards of certification which will require passing a national ethics exam and submitting references from employers who attest to your character and professional competence. Once admitted, you must then pass four rigorous parts of the Uniform CPA Examination covering topics related to accounting, auditing, taxes and business law. Finally, most states require CPAs to fulfill continuing education credits each year to maintain their license. 
In summary, becoming a CPA involves meeting academic standards, gaining relevant work experience, taking the Uniform CPA Examination and complying with any additional licensing requirements set by individual states. It generally takes between two and five years to achieve this goal but may vary based upon your level of education and prior experience.

instruction: I want to talk about "Smooth",  a song by Rob Thomas.
output_1: "Smooth" is a song by Rob Thomas, released as the third single from his 1999 solo debut album, "Something to Be". The song features a duet with singer Santana and reached the top of the Billboard Hot 100 chart in 1999, staying there for twelve weeks. The song won three Grammy Awards: Record of the Year, Song of the Year, and Best Pop Collaboration with Vocals. The song has been covered by many artists, including Glee, Bruno Mars, and even a cappella group Pentatonix. The song has become a classic, with its catchy chorus and unforgettable guitar solo.
output_2:
Rob Thomas's hit single “Smooth” was released in October of 1999 and quickly became one of the most popular songs of the year, reaching number one on Billboard’s Hot 100 chart for five weeks straight. The song has since become iconic as it helped launch Thomas into stardom and cemented his place in music history. It also featured some of the best collaborations between two artists ever seen with Carlos Santana joining forces with Thomas to create this timeless classic.

The lyrics of “Smooth” are simple yet powerful; they tell the story of a man who finds himself falling head over heels for someone special but isn’t sure if their feelings will be reciprocated. He knows there’s nothing he can do except hope for the best and take things day-by-day. This relatable sentiment resonates deeply with listeners and makes them feel connected to the narrator. On top of that, the instrumental of the track is absolutely captivating - featuring a mix of Latin percussion, electric guitars, and smooth saxophone riffs. All these elements come together perfectly to make what many consider to be one of the greatest love songs of all time.

Overall, “Smooth” is a masterpiece from start to finish. From its heartfelt lyrical content to its unforgettable melody and stellar production, it stands out among other hits of the late ‘90s and early 2000s. Its legacy continues to live on today through countless covers and remixes, proving just how much impact it had when it first came out nearly twenty years ago.

instruction: I'd like you to write me a story in the style of Don Delillo, about a bunch of immortal cats living in a New York high-rise co-op.  Go ahead and start a draft!

instruction: I like to host guests at my home from time to time, and I am gathering  recipes of different dishes and drinks to keep things interesting. I am interested in trying some Bolivian dishes. Can you give me a recipe for Chola Sandwich?
output_1:
Ingredients:

- 2 tablespoons of mayonnaise
- 2 slices of ham
- 2 slices of thick cut bacon
- 1/4 cup of Bolivian chola (a type of pickled onion)
- 2 slices of tomato
- 2 slices of cheese (your choice)

Instructions:
1. Toast the bread slices in a toaster or in a skillet.

3. Layer the ham, bacon, chola, tomato, and cheese on one of the slices of bread.

6. Grill the sandwich in a skillet or in a sandwich maker.

output_2:

- 1/4 cup mayonnaise

- 1 teaspoon garlic powder
